Part 1
Create position vector
The rules for the first part are:

The toboggan can only follow a few specific slopes (you opted for a cheaper model that prefers rational numbers); start by counting all the trees you would encounter for the slope right 3, down 1.



start_i <- 1
start_j <- 1

delta_i <- 1
delta_j <- 3



Duplicate the matrix
We need to have at least as many columns as rows.


times <- ceiling(dim(m)[1] / dim(m)[2]) * delta_j
m <- matrix(rep(m, times), ncol = times * ncol(m), byrow = F)

i <- seq((start_i + delta_i), nrow(m), by = delta_i) # lines
j <- seq((start_j + delta_j), ncol(m), by = delta_j) # columns

Part 2
The second part is exactly the same as for part 1 but with different rules (or scenarios).
Right 1, down 1.
Right 3, down 1. (This is the slope you already checked.)
Right 5, down 1.
Right 7, down 1.
Right 1, down 2.
Lets turn the previous code into a function.


count_trees <- function(delta_i, delta_j, m, start_i, start_j) {
  times <- ceiling(dim(m)[1] / dim(m)[2]) * delta_j
  m <- matrix(rep(m, times), ncol = times * ncol(m), byrow = F)

  i <- seq((start_i + delta_i), nrow(m), by = delta_i) # lines
  j <- seq((start_j + delta_j), ncol(m), by = delta_j) # columns

  j <- j[1:length(i)]

  object <- m[cbind(i, j)]

  ntrees <- sum(str_count(object, "#"), na.rm = TRUE)

  return(ntrees)
}



Now we can define the three new scenarios:


# Define the scenarios
right <- c(1, 3, 5, 7, 1)
down <- c(1, 1, 1, 1, 2)
start_i <- 1
start_j <- 1

file <- here("data", "input", "day3.txt")
x <- read_lines(file)
m <- str_split(x, pattern = "") %>%
  do.call(rbind, .)

trees <- pmap_int(
  list(down, right),
  count_trees,
  m = m,
  start_i = start_i,
  start_j = start_j
)

[11] "FFBFBBFRLR" "FBBFFFFRRR" "BFBFFBFRRL" "FFFBBFFLLL" "FFFFBBFLLL"
[16] "FFBFFBBRLL" "FBBBBBFLRR" "FFFBFFFLRR" "FBBBBBFRLR" "BFFBFFBLRL"

Here I am going to create a recursive function that splits the index vector into the upper or lower half.


find_index <- function(letter, index_range) {

  # F: the lower half
  # B: the upper half

  l <- str_sub(letter, 1, 1)

  if (length(index_range) == 1) {
    return(index_range)
  }

  if (l == "F" | l == "L") {
    start <- 1
    end <- ceiling(length(index_range) / 2)
    index_range <- index_range[start:end]
  } else if (l == "B" | l == "R") {
    start <- floor((length(index_range) / 2) + 1)
    end <- length(index_range)
    index_range <- index_range[start:end]
  }

  find_index(str_sub(letter, 2, end), index_range)
}



Part 1
Find the row and column numbers.


find_seat_id <- function(x, row_range, col_range) {

  i <- str_sub(x, 1, 7)
  i <- find_index(x, index_range)

  j <- str_sub(x, -3, -1)
  j <- find_index(j, col_range)

  return(i * 8 + j)
}
